== Provider API Implementations ==

The social media provider integrations (Twitter/X, Facebook Pages,
Instagram Business, LinkedIn) are implemented from scratch based on
official API documentation provided by each platform:

- Twitter/X API v2: https://developer.twitter.com/en/docs/twitter-api
- Facebook Graph API: https://developers.facebook.com/docs/pages-api
- Instagram Graph API: https://developers.facebook.com/docs/instagram-api
- LinkedIn API v2: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/linkedin/marketing

These implementations are original PHP/Laravel code and are not derived
from any specific third-party library or project. The OAuth flows, API
endpoint URLs, and request/response formats follow each provider's
official documentation.

== Inspiration ==

The UX design and feature set of remixpost draws inspiration from
open source social media management tools including Mixpost
(inovector/mixpost) and Postiz (gitroomhq/postiz-app). remixpost is an
independent implementation written from scratch with its own codebase,
architecture, and design.
